Andre Villas-Boas is a gamble - Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink
Media playback is not supported on this deviceFormer Chelsea striker Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink says it is "refreshing" that owner Roman Abramovich has invested so much faith in an upcoming talent like Andre Villas-Boas.Hasselbaink believes that the 33-year-old can "grow" with Chelsea, but feels it is unfair to compare him with mentor Jose Mourinho.Former Porto coach Villas-Boas signed a three-year-deal to take over at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday, succeeding Carlo Ancelotti as manager.